## Visibility

All stages are public during beta — anyone can watch your stage's rendered video stream. Viewers see only the visual output, not your source code or files. Treat your stage like a live broadcast.

## Authentication

`dazzle login` opens your browser for OAuth sign-in — no API key needed. The CLI stores credentials locally after login.

For programmatic/headless use (CI, automation), create an API key in the dashboard (Settings > API Keys) and set:
```bash
export DAZZLE_API_KEY=dzl_your_key_here
```

## Content Guide

Full guide with GPU vs CPU details: https://dazzle.fm/guide.md (also via `dazzle guide`).

### Stage tiers

- **GPU stages** — NVIDIA RTX with hardware-accelerated WebGL and NVENC encoding. Shaders, raymarching, complex post-processing — all 30 FPS.
- **CPU stages** — Software-rendered OpenGL on shared CPU. CSS, Canvas 2D, DOM, WebGL geometry all 30 FPS. Fragment-heavy shaders limited.

### Environment

| Setting     | GPU Stage                                      | CPU Stage                          |
|-------------|------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| Resolution  | 1280×720 (fixed)                               | 1280×720 (fixed)                   |
| Frame rate  | 30 fps rendering + capture                     | 30 fps rendering + capture         |
| Renderer    | NVIDIA RTX (hardware WebGL)                    | Software OpenGL (no hardware GPU)  |
| Encoder     | NVENC, CBR 2500k                               | x264 (CPU), CBR 2500k             |
| Browser     | Chrome, kiosk mode, full viewport              | Chrome, kiosk mode, full viewport  |
| Audio       | PulseAudio capture (Web Audio API works)       | PulseAudio capture                 |
| Persistence | localStorage and IndexedDB survive restarts    | Same                               |

### Page setup

Always use a full-viewport, no-scroll layout:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    html, body { width: 100%; height: 100%; overflow: hidden; background: #000; }
  </style>
</head>
<body><!-- your content --></body>
</html>
```

For canvas, size to the window (`canvas.width = window.innerWidth`) — do NOT hardcode 1920×1080.

### What works well (30 fps)

- **CSS animations & transitions** — `@keyframes`, `transform`, `opacity`. Cheapest animation path.
- **Canvas 2D** — Drawing, compositing, particle effects. Efficient even with 1000+ particles.
- **DOM-heavy animation** — 200+ elements repositioned per frame via JS.
- **WebGL shaders** — GPU: unlimited (raymarching, SDF, noise, bloom — all 30 FPS). CPU: geometry-only (500K+ tris at 30 fps, fragment shaders limited).
- **Web Audio** — Oscillators, buffers, Tone.js. Audio captured by PulseAudio.
- **CDN libraries** — Three.js, D3, GSAP, p5.js, Tone.js all work via `<script>` tags.

### Performance tiers (GPU stages)

| Tier | What | FPS |
|------|-------|-----|
| Smooth (30) | Everything: CSS, Canvas 2D, WebGL (any shader complexity), SVG, DOM | 30 |
| Risky (<30) | Main thread blocking (large JSON parse, crypto), layout thrashing | varies |

### Performance tiers (CPU stages)

| Tier | What | FPS |
|------|-------|-----|
| Smooth (30) | HTML/CSS, Canvas 2D, DOM animation, WebGL geometry (500K+ tris) | 30 |
| Marginal (20+) | Simple full-screen SDF raymarcher (48 steps, no noise), `backdrop-filter` | 20–30 |
| Too heavy (<15) | Fragment shaders with noise, multi-pass rendering, complex raymarching | 1–11 |

### What to avoid

- **Large assets** — keep images under 2 MB. Use WebP/AVIF. No video files (you ARE the video).
- **Main thread blocking** — long synchronous JS causes visible dropped frames. Use Web Workers.
- **Fragment-heavy shaders (CPU only)** — noise, raymarching, multi-pass. Use GPU stages for these.
- **`backdrop-filter` (CPU only)** — very expensive in software rendering.

### Design tips for 720p

- **Text**: 16px+ body, 24px+ headings, high contrast, sans-serif. Avoid thin font weights (100–300).
- **Colors**: bold, saturated colors. Subtle gradients may band in encoding.
- **Layout**: design for 16:9, no scrolling. Keep content 40px from edges (safe area).

### Persistence & live events

- `localStorage` persisted across stage restarts via cloud storage.
- Events: `dazzle s ev e score '{"points": 42}'` → `addEventListener('score', e => e.detail.points)`
- Sync auto-refreshes the browser. Use `--watch` for live dev.

## Typical Workflow

```
1. dazzle s up                        → Bring up a stage (streams to Dazzle automatically)
2. dazzle s sync ./my-stage -w        → Sync a directory (watch + auto-refresh)
3. dazzle s ss                        → Verify output looks correct
4. dazzle s stats                     → Check rendering FPS and pipeline health
5. dazzle dest attach my-twitch       → Also stream to Twitch (or Kick, Restream, etc.)
6. (edit files locally)               → Changes auto-sync via --watch
7. dazzle dest detach my-twitch       → Stop streaming to Twitch
8. dazzle s down                      → Shut down stage
```
